Project Rules for QR Attendance System

This application supports both Web and Android APK.

Architecture Rules:
- Backend (Node.js + Express) must handle all business logic
- Frontend (React Web / Mobile) should only handle UI
- All features must be API-based and reusable

API Rules:
- Use common APIs for both web and mobile
- Response format:
  { success: true, message: "", data: {} }

Features:
- QR code must be time-based (expiry required)
- Prevent multiple attendance submissions
- Validate student location (latitude, longitude)
- Attendance marking must be backend-controlled

Code Rules:
- Do not write logic only for web (avoid window/document in logic)
- Keep reusable functions
- Follow clean folder structure:
  /client
  /server
  /mobile (future)

UI Rules:
- Dashboard = summary only
- View Attendance = detailed data
- Avoid duplicate content across pages

Performance:
- Optimize for mobile responsiveness
- Avoid heavy UI components for APK
